{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/feverish-children-management/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"6c9dbc48-ffb5-5d52-85bf-52b12f444bcb","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 7a613c15-087d-417d-b008-a7f2018959f6 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 7a613c15-087d-417d-b008-a7f2018959f6 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d2579715-27ed-4ecb-9dba-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field ab16b2c9-222f-4ba8-a768-a7f2018959f6 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field ab16b2c9-222f-4ba8-a768-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- begin field dae1fdc8-5718-4e46-a2a2-a7f2018959f6 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field dae1fdc8-5718-4e46-a2a2-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- begin field 03387fa0-5089-43d2-b340-a7f2018959f6 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 03387fa0-5089-43d2-b340-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- begin field ebf35507-45b1-4d71-b8a8-a7f2018959f6 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field ebf35507-45b1-4d71-b8a8-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- begin field 656c1565-0d97-43bc-ac91-a7f2018959f6 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 656c1565-0d97-43bc-ac91-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- begin field a79e4edf-86db-4863-88bd-a7f2018959f6 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field a79e4edf-86db-4863-88bd-a7f2018959f6 --><!-- end item d2579715-27ed-4ecb-9dba-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"57afe72a-44a7-59f4-8b36-6eb7a2a98627","topicId":"cad66ea8-fd1e-4e8e-8a0a-4373743b9757","topicName":"Feverish children - management","slug":"feverish-children-management","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2018","chapters":[{"id":"37563924-9b7f-5010-ac82-0a34cfebfade","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d6888baa-d127-575e-8a84-9dc99c5a3fc7","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cd28b465-db51-5aaa-a791-4edb2d2190b9","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"2d5e04dc-f0b0-5c21-8aa0-e3dae4707252","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"214e8c64-9ed6-54f9-80fc-05f388a4efad","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"bc5b7055-3b0e-5b8e-af94-087af7c8df52","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"8a12ce09-3e70-5d55-a94e-0bb219807058","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8fb8cc12-0b57-52bd-81a1-f665491b6461","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e816954e-05aa-518b-9149-859f2eddaf82","slug